The federal government will be investing $ 4.1 million on a TV drama which is set to broadcast overseas as a way of deterring asylum seekers from entering Australian shores by boat .
ABC program will be shown in countries such as Syria , Iraq and Afghanistan later in the year , urging asylum seekers not to trust people smugglers .
The drama will reportedly have a story-line which involves the Australian Navy and asylum seekers .
Prime Minister Tony Abbott stated that only the Coalition would be able to stop asylum seeker boats .